description:
Soul of Sri Lankan Hip-Hop and Rap!
Rap Artist @ Ghozt Gang.

Chamath Janaka Perera is a mouthful when it comes to the rapper‚Äôs stage name FILL-T, hailing from Moratuwa, his native place where merry making and soul music is part of the spirit, Chamath has much talent to boast of in his career as a singer. His first song ‚ÄòMalpettak‚Äô included in the video has the rendition of ‚ÄòAmma‚Äô, ‚ÄòMoonlight Queen‚Äô and ‚ÄòPem Keruwata‚Äô. Contributing to the popular maiden album in Iraj‚Äôs ‚Äì ‚Äòyalpanam‚Äô, he has been featured with K.Sujeewa, Hasanjith, Madanee and Doggy Nation.

Chanaka also has two songs for news and home movie called Lawariz and Suwariz. His ambition as a solo artiste comes true when his solo album of 16 songs is released in the near future. The tracks for which is been done by Milan Fernando, Aruna Lian, Hiran Thenuwara, Slacker (Eranga), Mahesh and Gimantha Aponso. Lyrics by Wasantha Dugganarala, Kalum Srimal, Hiran Thenuwara and Shakthi. The first song released by the album is ‚ÄòParty Started‚Äô, a good radio hit among the Sri Lankan radio stations. The music produced by Milan Fernando and the rap part of the total album personally handled by Chamath is something to look forward to by rap fans.

‚ÄòMy latest song 'Nithambani‚Äô is played by the BBC channel which is played by the 6th Lane group with the rap parts done by me.

I have won the best hiphop outstanding act 2005 TNL onstage with my other crew K Pound.‚Äò Says Chamath, the guy inspired by Snoop Dogg, 2pac, Dr.Pre, Easy-E, N.W.A. and Dogg Pound. He considers them as legends and listening to these tapes he began writing his own lyrics. Further his expansion in working on songs is a spillover with the large group whom he works with for his first solo album are popular artistes, Naughty Doggy, Smokani, Wring Wrazer, K-Mac, Earth Quicker, Middle Finger, GT, Born Free, Lady Shi, Blunts and Alcohol.

Real Name : Chamath Perera 
Stage Name : Fill-t 
Band Name : 6th Lane 
School Attended : Prince Walles College - Moratuwa 
Inspired By : Snoop Dogg, 2Pac. N.W.A, Wu Tang 
Career Started On : 1995 - 1996 
Stage Performance : 250 - 300

Visually performed : Mal Paththak, Sandu raathri, Moon Light Queen, Amma, Pemkeruwata & Some Other

Coming Up : K Sujeewa's New #, My Solo album Video & will be launch my new album.

Producer's for my album : Mr Milan Fernando, Mr Aruna Lian, Mr Suneth Kelum, Mr Eranga, Mr Gimantha, Mr Mahesh, ( 6th Lane ) Mr Hiran & DJ LordX

Lyrics : Mr Nayananga, Mr Kelum Srimal, Mr Wasantha Dukgannarala, Mr GaJan & Mr Shakthi

Artist Featuring : Big Doggy, Naughty Doggy, Smokani, GT, Murder Dog, Pit bone, Blunts& Alcohol, K-Mac, Earth Quicker & K Sujeewa

Tiitle of Performed : Violence, Politics, Street, Love, Watz Real Hip-Hop

Releashed # : Party Started, Yowunvee, Meedhum Salu, Party on da mat.

Performed by feature movie : Lawaris & Suwaris.

Achievements : TNL on stage " Best Outstanding Hip-Hop Act 2005 " - K Pound ( was leader and controlled of the band)
